> This chicken linguine in creamy cheesy sauce is the perfect easy weeknight meal. A no-stress recipe that's simple, satisfying, and ready in less than 30 minutes.

Boil a #large pot{} of @water{to taste} with @salt{to taste} for the linguine.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the oil is hot, add the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%grams} to the pan and season with salt and @pepper{to taste}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

When boiling, add the @Dried Linguine{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the #pot{}.

Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(chopped into small pieces).

Peel and grate the @Garlic{2}(grated or use a garlic press).

Trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{1}(thinly sliced).

Roughly chop the @Mushrooms{150%grams}(roughly chopped).

Add the onion, garlic, half the @Italian Herbs{½%sachet} and mushrooms to the chicken.

Stir occasionally, until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pour in @Creme Fraiche{125%grams} and 100ml water (double for 4p).

Simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @Grated Italian Style Hard Cheese{25%grams} and allow to melt through the sauce.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Stir the linguine into the sauce and allow to warm through.

Divide the pasta between bowls.

Serve topped with sliced scallions.